<section class="block-paragraph">
<h2 data-block-key="lznkg">5. Continue investing</h2><p data-block-key="2s0qu">Here&#x27;s one of the biggest secrets of investing, courtesy of the Oracle of Omaha himself, Warren Buffett. You do not need to do extraordinary things to get extraordinary results. (Note: <a href="https://www.fool.com/investing/how-to-invest/famous-investors/warren-buffett-investments/">Warren Buffett</a> is not only the most successful long-term investor of all time, but also one of the best sources of wisdom for your <a href="https://www.fool.com/investing/how-to-invest/stocks/investment-strategies/">investment strategy</a>.)</p><p data-block-key="1jes5">The most surefire way to make money in the stock market is to <a href="https://www.fool.com/investing/how-to-invest/stocks/how-many-shares-buy-stock/">buy shares</a> of great businesses at reasonable prices and hold on to the <a href="https://www.fool.com/investing/how-to-invest/stocks/stock-v-share/">shares</a> for as long as the businesses remain great (or until you need the money). If you do this, you&#x27;ll experience some <a href="https://www.fool.com/investing/how-to-invest/stocks/stock-market-volatility/">volatility</a> along the way, but over time you&#x27;ll produce excellent investment returns.</p>
</section>
